# React and R3F patterns

## React

- Prefer **function components** with hooks. Most feature code currently lives in [src/App.tsx](src/App.tsx); when you add substantial UI or behavior, **extract** components or hooks under `src/` instead of inflating `App.tsx` without reason.
- Keep **local state** in the component that owns the UX (sim time, lat/lon, facing, view mode) unless you introduce a deliberate shared layer.

## React Three Fiber and drei

- Use **`<Canvas>`** from `@react-three/fiber` for WebGL scenes; use **`useThree`** when you need the camera or gl (see `CameraRig` in `App.tsx`).
- Use **drei** for helpers already in the project: `OrbitControls`, `Stars`, `useTexture`, `Line`, etc. Prefer existing patterns over new abstractions.
- Prefer **`useMemo`** / **`useEffect`** for expensive setup (orbit samples, texture clones) rather than recomputing every render.
- Use **`useFrame`** only when you need per-frame animation or continuous updates; the orbit view does not require it for static time steps.

## Three.js

- Import types and classes from **`three`** (`Vector3`, `Quaternion`, `Color`, `SRGBColorSpace`, materials, etc.).
- For **color textures**, set `colorSpace = SRGBColorSpace` and `needsUpdate = true` on cloned maps where the codebase already does (Earth/Moon meshes).

## Testing

- This repo **does not** ship a test runner today. Do not assume Vitest or Testing Library. If tests are added, document the chosen tool in AGENTS.md and this rule.
